  "body": "# Problem\r\n\r\nIn its current incarnation, the Activity Center (AC) unread badge (blue dot icon) always appears when there's a new notification.\r\n\r\nMany users won't open the AC and judiciously mark notifications as read, but they'll open the AC nonetheless to see if something requires their attention. For such users, the unread badge will be visible most of the time, which makes the badge less useful in its goal of helping them see what requires their attention.\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\n\r\nThe new design should change the unread badge to behave in a more subtle way:\r\n\r\n1. Blue indicator when there's a new notification **since the user last opened the AC**.\r\n2. Gray indicator if the user opened and closed the AC and no new notification has arrived yet, but there are still unread notifications.\r\n3. No indicator if all notifications are read.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/46027/213872736-21c16c45-f42a-4aae-b767-a9251f678096.png\" width=\"700\" />\r\n\r\n## Notes\r\n\r\n- Dispatch calls to `:activity-center.notifications/fetch-unread-count` will probably need to change.\r\n\r\n## References\r\n\r\n- https://www.figma.com/file/eDfxTa9IoaCMUy5cLTp0ys/Shell-for-Mobile?node-id=5305%3A521993&t=wwEILzdU13eKAvtW-0",
